1189年–1199年","AFT. 1216":"1216年之後","1216":"1216年","BET. 1199 - 1216":"從1199年1月8日到1217年1月7日","1225":"1225年","1189":"1189年","BEF. 1199":"1199年之前","AFT. 1199":"1199年之後","1199":"1199年","1230":"1230年","lifeSummary":"Peter Duke是Roger le Duc的兒子，於1199年之前出生。他至少有1個兒子。他去世於1216年之後。"},"zh-hans":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"1199年之前–1216年之后","1199–1216":"1199年–1216年","1225–1230":"1225年–1230年","1189–1199":"1189年–1199年","AFT. 1216":"1216年之后","1216":"1216年","BET. 1199 - 1216":"从1199年1月8日到1217年1月7日","1225":"1225年","1189":"1189年","BEF. 1199":"1199年之前","AFT. 1199":"1199年之后","1199":"1199年","1230":"1230年","lifeSummary":"Peter Duke是Roger le Duc的儿子，于1199年之前出生。他至少有1个儿子。他去世于1216年之后。"},"hr":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"prije 1199.–nakon 1216.","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"nakon 1216.","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"od 8. siječnja 1199. do 7. siječnja 1217.","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"prije 1199.","AFT. 1199":"nakon 1199.","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"cs":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"před 1199–po 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"po 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"od 8. ledna 1199 do 7. ledna 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"před 1199","AFT. 1199":"po 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"da":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"før 1199–efter 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"efter 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"fra 8. januar 1199 til 7. januar 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"før 1199","AFT. 1199":"efter 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"nl":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"vóór 1199–na 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"na 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"van 8 januari 1199 to 7 januari 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"vóór 1199","AFT. 1199":"na 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"en":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"before 1199–after 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"after 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"from 8 January 1199 to 7 January 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"before 1199","AFT. 1199":"after 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Duke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>duk(ke)</i>, <i>duck</i>, <i>doke</i>, <i>dook</i> ‘duck’ (Old English <i>dūce</i>), either from a perceived resemblance (perhaps a waddling gait) or from association with wild fowling. Compare   Duck  ,   Drake  .","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Duk</i> or <i>Duke</i>. In northern England this is usually a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>. It may alternatively be a survival of one or more Old English personal names, though it is uncertain whether they were still current in the period of surname formation. Old English <i>Ducc(a)</i> is attested in placenames like Duxford (Cambridgeshire) and Duckington (Cheshire), and was perhaps interchangeable with <i>Docc</i>, attested in Doxey (Staffordshire) and Doxford (Northumberland). <i>Duke</i> could also represent Old English <i>Deowuc</i> (as in Deuxhill, Shropshire). A surname from <i>Marmaduke</i> is on record until at least 1881 and derives from the personal name <i>Marmaduke</i>, apparently an Anglo-Norman French pronunciation of Old Irish <i>Maolmaedóc</i> ‘devotee of <i>Maedóc</i>’; see   Duckett  .","Americanized form of Polish <b>Duk</b>: nickname from <i>dukać</i> ‘to stammer or falter’."],"variants":[{"name":"Dock","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Duke  .","Norwegian: habitational name from a farm named Dokk, from Old Norse <i>dǫkk</i> ‘hollow, depression’.","North German (Lower Saxony): possibly a metonymic occupational name for someone who worked in the cloth trade, from Middle Low German <i>dōk</i> ‘fabric’."]},{"name":"Doke","meanings":["English: variant of   Duke  ."]},{"name":"Duch","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Nga, Phal, Phan, Sophan, Tha, Thang, Yen.  German Kurt, Klaus.","Polish, Sorbian, and Ukrainian: nickname from <i>duch</i> ‘spirit, breath’.","Czech: from a short form of the Old Czech personal name <i>Duchoslav</i>, composed of the elements <i>duch</i> ‘spirit’ + <i>slav</i> ‘glory’ or ‘famous’."]},{"name":"Duckett","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): from the Middle English personal name <i>Duket</i>. This may sometimes have been an early Middle English pet form of an Old English <i>Ducc(a)</i>, but was more often a pet form of <i>Marmaduke</i>, especially in Yorkshire (see   Duke  ). <i>Marmaduke</i> itself is from Irish <i>Maol Maedóc</i> ‘servant of Maedóc’, <i>Maedóc</i> being the name of prominent Irish saints of the 6th and 7th centuries."]},{"name":"Duck","meanings":["English: variant of   Duke  .","Irish: adoption of the English name (see 1 above) as an equivalent of <b>Lohan</b> (an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Leocháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Leochán</i>’) by mistranslation, as if from <i>lacha</i> ‘duck’.","North German (also <b>Dück</b>) and German (<b>Dück</b>): see   Dueck  ."]},{"name":"Dukes","meanings":["English: variant of   Duke  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peter Duke was born before 1199 as the son of Roger le Duc. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1216."},"et":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"enne 1199–pärast 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"pärast 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"8. jaanuar 1199 kuni 7. jaanuar 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"enne 1199","AFT. 1199":"pärast 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"fi":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"ennen vuotta 1199–1216 jälkeen","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"1216 jälkeen","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"vuodesta 8. tammikuuta 1199 vuoteen 7. tammikuuta 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"ennen vuotta 1199","AFT. 1199":"1199 jälkeen","1199":"1199","1230":"1230"},"fr":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"avant 1199–après 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"après 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"du 8 janvier 1199 au 7 janvier 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"avant 1199","AFT. 1199":"après 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230","lifeSummary":"Peter Duke est né avant 1199, fils de Roger le Duc. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1216."},"de":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"vor 1199–nach 1216","1199–1216":"1199–1216","1225–1230":"1225–1230","1189–1199":"1189–1199","AFT. 1216":"nach 1216","1216":"1216","BET. 1199 - 1216":"von 8. Januar 1199 bis 7. Januar 1217","1225":"1225","1189":"1189","BEF. 1199":"vor 1199","AFT. 1199":"nach 1199","1199":"1199","1230":"1230","lifeSummary":"Peter Duke wurde vor 1199, als Sohn von Roger le Duc geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb nach 1216."},"ht":{"BEF. 1199–AFT. 1216":"before 1199